&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a small IT department with a clear focus on delivering IT services to frontline clinicians. We are agile, focusing on getting solutions right first time and applying appropriate best practice to ensure effective delivery of IT projects. We are a developing team looking to continually improve and are currently looking for a IT Project Support Officer who can deliver real change and make a difference.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is a lot to do so you must be dynamic and be able to champion and lead change. The post holder will be responsible for managing and supporting multiple IT projects and work packages, ensuring work is planned, co-ordinated, and delivered within agreed timelines and to budget, using effective project management approaches and tools.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As an evolving team we are looking for colleagues who will use their experience to contribute suggestions for improvement, so effective collaborative working is a key skill required within the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role involves the management of third-party suppliers, so good interpersonal skills, stakeholder management and direct experience of working with external stakeholders is important.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder should be highly organised, able to prioritise their own workload and have excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Although the post is based at our Cleckheaton Office you will be required to travel across Kirklees on a regular basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information about the role please contact Matt Spencer (IT Project Delivery Manager) on 030 3330 9288 or at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;matt.spencer@locala.org.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
